Scottish independent schools maintain a curriculum of academic excellence and this continued in 2018 with another series of outstanding exam results, enhanced by individual and collective success in sport, art, music and other collective efforts.
With over 30,000 pupils throughout Scotland, these schools, represented by The Scottish Council of Independent Schools (SCIS), aim to provide the best level of service to their students and parents.
Independent schools aim to prepare pupils for later higher education, their chosen career and place in the world as global citizens.
As an education sector able to develop and adopt a personalized school study plan, we note that modern languages continue to be a popular and required subject within schools.
Nelson Mandela said, "If you speak to a man in a language he understands, the message will reach his brain.
If you speak to him in his mother tongue, the message will reach the heart."
